==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Moolley
<hw>Mool"ley</hw> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[CF. Gael. <ets>maolag</ets> a hornless cow,
<ets>maol</ets> bald, hornless, blunt.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A mulley
or polled animal.</def> <mark>[U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cow.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.; U.S., a child's
word.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Leave milking and dry up old <qex>mulley</qex>, thy cow.</q>
<rj><qau>Tusser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

